article.headline: Wright helps Penn State to win in preseason WNIT
article.linkText: Key second-half run lifts No. 14 Penn State
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Tanisha Wright scored eight of her 19
points during a key second-half run as No. 14-ranked Penn State
beat Bucknell 86-72 Friday night in the opening round of the
preseason WNIT.

	   Molly Creamer had 11 points, including three long 3-pointers,
during a 19-9 run that brought Bucknell (0-1) to 55-51 with 14:05
left.

	   Creamer went to the bench with her fourth foul with 13:07 left,
however, and Wright scored eight consecutive points for Penn State
(1-0) during a 13-6 run that gave Penn State a 68-57 lead and
put the game out of reach.

	   Kelly Mazzante, the nation's scoring leader last year, had 25
points for Penn State, which advances to face Siena, an 83-66
winner over Syracuse. Jess Brungo scored 18 points, and Jess Strom
had 10.

	   Bucknell took its only lead, 20-19, after Creamer's 3-pointer
and two free throws by Jennie Ruth. But Jennifer Brenden and Brungo
both hit 3-pointers a 14-2 run that put the Lady Lions up for good.

	   Creamer led the Bison with 28 points, and Desire Almind added 26
points and 10 rebounds.
